1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:01,433
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,433 --> 00:00:02,700
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:12,900 --> 00:00:14,100
(Episode 69)

4
00:00:22,600 --> 00:00:23,600
Mom.

5
00:00:29,900 --> 00:00:30,900
Mom.

6
00:00:35,033 --> 00:00:36,033
Mom.

7
00:00:37,600 --> 00:00:40,200
Yeon Sun.

8
00:00:44,133 --> 00:00:45,200
What took you so long?

9
00:00:47,900 --> 00:00:49,200
Do you know how long I've waited?

10
00:00:51,600 --> 00:00:52,600
"Maybe she'll come today."

11
00:00:53,800 --> 00:00:55,000
"She'll definitely come tomorrow."

12
00:00:57,133 --> 00:01:00,233
One day became ten.

13
00:01:00,933 --> 00:01:02,233
Ten days became a month.

14
00:01:03,633 --> 00:01:08,200
A year became 20, then 30.

15
00:01:10,200 --> 00:01:12,533
And now it's been 50 years.

16
00:01:14,133 --> 00:01:15,133
I'm sorry.

17
00:01:16,400 --> 00:01:18,900
I came far too late, didn't I?

18
00:01:20,300 --> 00:01:22,500
It was all my fault, Yeon Sun.

19
00:01:25,600 --> 00:01:28,900
Don't say you're sorry.
Don't say it was your fault.

20
00:01:30,900 --> 00:01:31,933
I got tired of waiting.

21
00:01:33,300 --> 00:01:34,600
I hated you. I resented you.

22
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:37,533
In the end,
I convinced myself you were dead.

23
00:01:38,500 --> 00:01:41,600
So why now? Why now?

24
00:01:42,300 --> 00:01:44,233
You say you've spent your whole life
looking for me.

25
00:01:45,500 --> 00:01:47,500
What am I supposed to do then?

26
00:01:48,833 --> 00:01:50,933
Now you make me a birthday meal,

27
00:01:52,533 --> 00:01:56,000
when I've grown old
without even knowing my real birthday.

28
00:01:56,600 --> 00:01:59,033
I just feel so sorry for myself.

29
00:01:59,300 --> 00:02:01,600
Yeon Sun.

30
00:02:02,100 --> 00:02:03,533
Yeon Sun, I'm sorry.

31
00:02:03,533 --> 00:02:06,400
It was all my fault. I'm sorry.

32
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:40,400
Is it your mother's birthday today?

33
00:02:41,700 --> 00:02:42,733
I guess so.

34
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:45,600
The birthday we know is in February,

35
00:02:46,533 --> 00:02:48,300
but I guess today is her real birthday.

36
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:52,000
What's wrong?

37
00:02:53,533 --> 00:02:55,900
Why are you all out here?
Why aren't you inside?

38
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:59,200
Mom and Grandma are out in the yard.

39
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:03,600
I think it's Mom's birthday today.

40
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:05,400
What?

41
00:03:05,933 --> 00:03:07,800
What are you talking about?

42
00:03:08,233 --> 00:03:10,033
Her birthday was ages ago.

43
00:03:11,200 --> 00:03:15,033
Your mom was adopted
and returned over and over,

44
00:03:16,133 --> 00:03:19,033
and her records were completely changed,
so she never knew her real birthday.

45
00:03:20,900 --> 00:03:22,400
So today is the day.

46
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:36,500
What's wrong? You can't eat it?

47
00:03:38,133 --> 00:03:40,600
Have I made it impossible for you
to even eat seaweed soup?

48
00:03:41,500 --> 00:03:42,800
No, it's not that.

49
00:03:45,100 --> 00:03:47,200
It tastes just like I remember.

50
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:50,733
For the past 50 years,

51
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:54,233
every birthday morning,

52
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:58,733
I made seaweed soup
and flower pancakes for you.

53
00:04:02,233 --> 00:04:05,833
I never thought I'd see the day
you'd be eating them again.

54
00:04:08,833 --> 00:04:10,133
Thank you, my dear.

55
00:04:12,300 --> 00:04:13,333
"My dear."

56
00:04:19,400 --> 00:04:21,333
I loved it when you called me that.

57
00:04:23,833 --> 00:04:25,933
It felt like I was back in your womb,

58
00:04:27,300 --> 00:04:30,733
so warm and peaceful.

59
00:04:35,733 --> 00:04:37,733
When did you grow so old?

60
00:04:39,100 --> 00:04:41,200
In my memories, you were so young.

61
00:04:43,100 --> 00:04:45,233
And in my mind,

62
00:04:46,700 --> 00:04:48,800
you are still
my seven-year-old little girl.

63
00:04:51,400 --> 00:04:52,500
Have a bite with me.

64
00:04:55,300 --> 00:04:57,733
You were the one who went through
all that pain to give birth to me.

65
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:06,000
I'm happy just watching you eat.

66
00:05:07,233 --> 00:05:08,600
Go on, before it gets cold.

67
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:43,600
There.

68
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:45,000
You eat too.

69
00:05:51,400 --> 00:05:52,500
Thank you.

70
00:05:53,100 --> 00:05:54,700
Thank you.

71
00:06:04,200 --> 00:06:05,233
Seriously.

72
00:06:05,900 --> 00:06:08,333
We didn't even know
today was her real birthday,

73
00:06:08,333 --> 00:06:11,400
and here we were,
trying so hard to open that safe.

74
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:15,100
Honey, don't you think I'm brilliant?

75
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:18,433
The moment Father saw the seaweed soup
Mother made...

76
00:06:18,700 --> 00:06:21,500
and said, "So today's the day,"

77
00:06:21,500 --> 00:06:22,900
it all clicked.

78
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:25,500
Now we've got the safe's password.

79
00:06:26,200 --> 00:06:27,533
You're right.

80
00:06:27,533 --> 00:06:29,833
You're just getting smarter and smarter
these days.

81
00:06:29,833 --> 00:06:31,400
You're unstoppable.

82
00:06:31,733 --> 00:06:33,000
Very impressive.

83
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:38,233
Still, Father has to leave the room...

84
00:06:38,233 --> 00:06:40,433
before we can get to the safe.

85
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:43,133
Should we go tell him,

86
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:45,800
"Today's Kang Yeon Ja's birthday."

87
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:48,333
"Why don't you go
wish her a happy birthday?"

88
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:49,900
Maybe give him a little push?

89
00:06:51,400 --> 00:06:54,133
That's actually a great idea,
but won't it be too obvious?

90
00:06:54,700 --> 00:06:56,733
Father would see right through it.

91
00:07:00,333 --> 00:07:02,833
Where are you suddenly going...

92
00:07:02,833 --> 00:07:04,400
that you need the car?

93
00:07:05,300 --> 00:07:06,700
I'm going to Mr. Cho's house.

94
00:07:07,733 --> 00:07:09,600
Yeong Hwa's running very late,

95
00:07:10,500 --> 00:07:12,900
and I'm worried something
might've happened.

96
00:07:13,833 --> 00:07:15,400
Yes, let's go.

97
00:07:24,533 --> 00:07:26,000
My goodness!

98
00:07:26,500 --> 00:07:28,300
- This is huge!
- Amazing!

99
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:30,000
Let's go!

100
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:35,900
If I'd known this would happen,

101
00:07:36,533 --> 00:07:38,833
I would've changed
into my work clothes first.

102
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:41,100
Work clothes? What work clothes?

103
00:07:41,700 --> 00:07:45,133
I told you.
We're not just ordinary safecrackers.

104
00:07:45,733 --> 00:07:48,200
We're carrying out a mission
of great importance,

105
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:50,400
one that will reveal the future blueprint
of Kangsu Group.

106
00:07:50,400 --> 00:07:52,600
And we're doing it in our pajamas? Really?

107
00:07:53,400 --> 00:07:54,600
Should we go change now?

108
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:56,233
Quiet. We don't have time.

109
00:07:56,233 --> 00:07:57,900
Just hurry up and open it.

110
00:07:57,900 --> 00:08:01,233
Okay. Since today's July fourth...

111
00:08:01,500 --> 00:08:03,600
Try 0704. Hurry!

112
00:08:07,800 --> 00:08:10,800
Please enter the password
or use your fingerprint.

113
00:08:22,700 --> 00:08:24,100
Just hurry up and open it.

114
00:08:24,100 --> 00:08:25,933
I can't wait to see what's inside.

115
00:08:26,133 --> 00:08:28,333
Maybe a mountain of gold bars?

116
00:08:28,833 --> 00:08:30,800
The time limit has expired.

117
00:08:31,733 --> 00:08:33,633
It says the time ran out.
We have to start over.

118
00:08:33,633 --> 00:08:34,833
Hurry!

119
00:08:47,100 --> 00:08:48,100
That's it?

120
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:50,700
The chairman of Kangsu Group's safe...

121
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:52,300
doesn't even have a single gold bar?

122
00:08:52,500 --> 00:08:53,600
Come on.

123
00:08:53,900 --> 00:08:57,400
This envelope must contain Father's will,

124
00:08:57,900 --> 00:09:01,600
along with the future
of Kangsu Group's shares.

125
00:09:01,633 --> 00:09:03,200
Fine. Hurry and open it.

126
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:05,700
At this rate, I'm going to pass out.
Hurry!

127
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:11,400
I can't see it.

128
00:09:11,400 --> 00:09:12,900
- Hurry!
- All right. I'm taking it out.

129
00:09:12,900 --> 00:09:13,900
Here it comes.

130
00:09:28,033 --> 00:09:30,400
Happy birthday, Kang Yeon Ja.

131
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:33,600
Happy birthday, Grandma.

132
00:09:35,100 --> 00:09:37,000
Honey. You guys.

133
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:42,133
<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

134
00:09:42,133 --> 00:09:45,100
<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

135
00:09:45,400 --> 00:09:48,933
<i>- Dear Mother
- Dear Grandma</i>

136
00:09:49,200 --> 00:09:52,100
<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

137
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:55,600
Mom. Grandma.

138
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:58,700
Think of each candle
as ten years of the birthdays...

139
00:09:59,300 --> 00:10:01,900
you couldn't celebrate with each other...

140
00:10:01,900 --> 00:10:02,900
and blow them out together.

141
00:10:03,300 --> 00:10:05,600
Yes. Let's do it together, Yeon Sun.

142
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,300
One, two, three.

143
00:10:14,133 --> 00:10:16,500
- Doesn't it look delicious?
- Bit Na's the most excited.

144
00:10:16,733 --> 00:10:18,033
- Go ahead and dig in.
- Winner eats first?

145
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:20,000
Bit Na likes this.

146
00:10:22,500 --> 00:10:23,633
- Ms. Lee Yeong Hwa.
- Is it good?

147
00:10:24,600 --> 00:10:27,533
Congratulations from the bottom
of my heart on finding Yeon Sun.

148
00:10:29,300 --> 00:10:32,233
Happy birthday, Yeon Sun.

149
00:10:39,900 --> 00:10:41,500
Min Ho.

150
00:10:42,333 --> 00:10:44,200
You actually opened Grandpa's safe?

151
00:10:45,133 --> 00:10:46,800
What exactly are you trying to find?

152
00:10:47,333 --> 00:10:49,533
Well, your Grandpa's will...

153
00:10:49,533 --> 00:10:50,900
should be in this envelope.

154
00:10:50,900 --> 00:10:53,900
And it should also say
how his remaining 20 percent stake...

155
00:10:53,900 --> 00:10:56,400
will be divided.

156
00:10:56,500 --> 00:10:58,900
And what are you planning to do
once you know?

157
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:00,700
What do you mean?

158
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:02,700
If, as we feared, everything goes...

159
00:11:02,833 --> 00:11:05,900
to Grandma and her daughter,
we can't let that happen.

160
00:11:07,133 --> 00:11:09,833
We need to know in advance
so we can prepare.

161
00:11:10,233 --> 00:11:13,500
I told you. "Know your enemy
and know yourself, and you'll never lose."

162
00:11:13,700 --> 00:11:15,600
Dad, Mom.

163
00:11:17,300 --> 00:11:18,800
For the first time in my life,

164
00:11:19,700 --> 00:11:21,400
I'm ashamed to be your son.

165
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:24,133
I've been disappointed in you before,

166
00:11:25,100 --> 00:11:26,500
but never like this.

167
00:11:26,900 --> 00:11:30,600
How can you say something
so harsh? We only...

168
00:11:30,600 --> 00:11:31,933
Don't drag me into this anymore.

169
00:11:31,933 --> 00:11:35,133
Or I'll stop being your son.

170
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:37,600
All right.

171
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:39,200
I get it. That's enough.

172
00:11:44,233 --> 00:11:46,100
I'll never touch Grandpa's safe again.

173
00:11:46,933 --> 00:11:48,500
- I promise.
- Honey.

174
00:11:48,500 --> 00:11:50,100
How can you just leave?

175
00:11:53,600 --> 00:11:55,500
Fine. I'll go too.

176
00:11:57,733 --> 00:11:58,800
But Min Ho...

177
00:11:59,833 --> 00:12:01,600
Don't look at me like that again.

178
00:12:02,300 --> 00:12:04,300
They say nothing's scarier
than your own child.

179
00:12:05,300 --> 00:12:07,033
You scare me so much right now.

180
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:09,800
Honey.

181
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:29,900
It must've been an unavoidable accident
that Dad couldn't prevent.

182
00:12:32,833 --> 00:12:35,133
He must've lived with unbearable guilt
all these years.

183
00:12:37,300 --> 00:12:39,600
Seo Seung Ri,
Mom wants you to come eat some fruit.

184
00:12:44,300 --> 00:12:45,300
Are you crying?

185
00:12:46,100 --> 00:12:47,900
No, I'm not. Get out.

186
00:12:52,833 --> 00:12:54,900
It's been a while
since we've all been together like this.

187
00:12:55,933 --> 00:12:59,600
Everyone's been so busy
that we haven't even had a meal together.

188
00:13:00,400 --> 00:13:01,400
Especially Seo Seung Wu.

189
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:03,600
Yes, Seo Seung Wu reporting in.

190
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:06,300
Are you hiding something in your studio?

191
00:13:06,500 --> 00:13:07,900
Why is it so hard to see you these days?

192
00:13:08,400 --> 00:13:11,000
You used to complain
when I stayed home all day.

193
00:13:11,200 --> 00:13:12,833
Now you're complaining because I'm busy?

194
00:13:13,700 --> 00:13:14,800
That's not right.

195
00:13:16,233 --> 00:13:17,500
When's your webtoon coming out?

196
00:13:18,333 --> 00:13:19,333
Soon.

197
00:13:19,333 --> 00:13:21,900
We're already coordinating
the launch date with the platform.

198
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:26,200
You said you'd finished your task, Dad.

199
00:13:26,500 --> 00:13:28,000
Are things finally slowing down?

200
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:31,033
Yeah. I've got a lot more free time now.

201
00:13:31,233 --> 00:13:34,033
Dad, want to go for a walk with me?

202
00:13:34,500 --> 00:13:36,733
A walk? Sure.

203
00:13:42,100 --> 00:13:43,200
I'm sorry, Dad.

204
00:13:43,700 --> 00:13:44,700
For what?

205
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:49,000
I think I've been mean to you lately.

206
00:13:50,233 --> 00:13:52,800
I even threw a tantrum over what happened
on my first day of school.

207
00:13:54,333 --> 00:13:57,000
I'm really immature, aren't I?

208
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:00,000
No.

209
00:14:01,200 --> 00:14:04,633
I'm the one who's always sorry.
To Mom and all of you.

210
00:14:05,500 --> 00:14:08,700
Dad, if you fall, you just get back up.

211
00:14:09,500 --> 00:14:10,600
So promise me you will.

212
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:16,900
You remember what I told you
when I was six, right?

213
00:14:18,500 --> 00:14:21,500
From now on, whenever something's
troubling you or things get tough,

214
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:23,233
share it with us.

215
00:14:23,533 --> 00:14:25,300
Don't carry everything
on your own anymore.

216
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:28,800
You know me. I'm your daughter.

217
00:14:29,433 --> 00:14:31,133
I'm more capable than you think now.

218
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:33,600
Yeah.

219
00:14:34,833 --> 00:14:37,500
Just hearing that
makes me feel so reassured.

220
00:14:38,733 --> 00:14:39,800
I'm sorry, Dad.

221
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:43,100
I'm so sorry I even briefly wondered...

222
00:14:43,600 --> 00:14:47,133
whether you might be a bad person.

223
00:14:50,033 --> 00:14:51,633
You did the right thing today.

224
00:14:52,800 --> 00:14:54,600
Seeing you standing beside Mother...

225
00:14:55,300 --> 00:14:56,733
made me tear up so many times.

226
00:15:00,633 --> 00:15:03,400
Your eyes are all puffy.
You must've cried a lot.

227
00:15:05,600 --> 00:15:08,133
From now on, you can make up...

228
00:15:08,700 --> 00:15:11,500
for all those lost years tenfold,
no, a hundredfold.

229
00:15:12,700 --> 00:15:14,333
What do you mean, make up for them?

230
00:15:15,733 --> 00:15:18,433
The birthday seaweed soup
just caught me off guard.

231
00:15:18,433 --> 00:15:20,400
Nothing's changed overnight.

232
00:15:20,933 --> 00:15:24,233
Take it slow. Let time do its work.

233
00:15:26,400 --> 00:15:30,133
The more time you spend together,
the closer you'll become.

234
00:15:32,233 --> 00:15:33,800
You've been through so much, Yeon Ja.

235
00:15:34,833 --> 00:15:37,000
No, Yeon Sun.

236
00:15:37,833 --> 00:15:38,933
Seriously!

237
00:15:42,300 --> 00:15:43,400
Yeon Sun.

238
00:15:45,900 --> 00:15:48,600
I'm so glad Mom and Grandma made up.

239
00:15:49,800 --> 00:15:50,800
Me too.

240
00:15:51,400 --> 00:15:54,533
Your mother's wounds ran so deep,
I thought it would take much longer.

241
00:16:00,100 --> 00:16:01,100
Give me your phone.

242
00:16:01,933 --> 00:16:03,300
What? Why?

243
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:06,133
Just give it to me for a second.
You trust me, right?

244
00:16:07,133 --> 00:16:08,800
Now I trust you even less.

245
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:10,200
What,
are you going to hack it or something?

246
00:16:10,333 --> 00:16:11,400
You got me.

247
00:16:13,100 --> 00:16:15,133
I'll gladly let you.

248
00:16:15,400 --> 00:16:16,433
There's nothing on it anyway.

249
00:16:23,633 --> 00:16:24,633
There.

250
00:16:25,133 --> 00:16:26,133
Here you go.

251
00:16:26,300 --> 00:16:27,300
What did you do?

252
00:16:28,300 --> 00:16:29,600
I installed an app.

253
00:16:30,133 --> 00:16:32,300
It's the one I told you about,
Mind Post Office.

254
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:38,633
If you ever change your mind,

255
00:16:39,333 --> 00:16:42,200
think of it as sending yourself a letter
you could never write,

256
00:16:42,800 --> 00:16:44,933
and pour your heart out here.

257
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:50,333
I want to help somehow,

258
00:16:51,400 --> 00:16:54,500
but I'm not exactly
someone you can lean on.

259
00:16:54,900 --> 00:16:56,700
I'm not a doctor or a therapist either.

260
00:16:58,200 --> 00:17:01,700
This is all Developer Cho Eun Ae can do.

261
00:17:02,700 --> 00:17:05,133
Why wouldn't you be someone I can lean on?

262
00:17:05,533 --> 00:17:07,800
I'm leaning on you so much already.

263
00:17:07,900 --> 00:17:09,300
Every single day. Every moment.

264
00:17:10,100 --> 00:17:11,700
I knew it.

265
00:17:11,933 --> 00:17:13,433
I was just pretending to be humble.

266
00:17:23,533 --> 00:17:25,833
Grandma, your japchae is the best.

267
00:17:27,233 --> 00:17:30,133
Really? I didn't make it though.

268
00:17:30,433 --> 00:17:33,733
I forgot. Your mom made it.

269
00:17:34,400 --> 00:17:37,400
Then what do I call Grandma's mom?

270
00:17:38,500 --> 00:17:40,600
She's your great-grandmother,

271
00:17:40,600 --> 00:17:42,700
so you can just call her Great-Grandma.

272
00:17:42,700 --> 00:17:45,033
Great-Grandma.

273
00:17:45,333 --> 00:17:48,633
I think you inherited
your cooking skills from Grandma, Mom.

274
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:50,533
Everything's delicious.

275
00:17:50,633 --> 00:17:52,133
Team Manager
said something similar before.

276
00:17:52,900 --> 00:17:55,300
He said that Mom's cooking
was the second best in the world,

277
00:17:55,300 --> 00:17:56,800
and his grandma's was the best.

278
00:17:56,833 --> 00:17:57,833
What? When did I ever...

279
00:17:58,500 --> 00:18:00,133
I'm sorry, Mother.
Your cooking is the best.

280
00:18:00,133 --> 00:18:01,300
Good grief.

281
00:18:01,300 --> 00:18:04,533
Enough judging the food.
Eat up and get to work.

282
00:18:04,933 --> 00:18:05,933
Yes, Mom.

283
00:18:08,800 --> 00:18:10,600
- Here's some water.
- Thank you.

284
00:18:11,600 --> 00:18:13,700
But are you two really okay?

285
00:18:14,133 --> 00:18:16,133
You even saw Mom and Grandma's
emotional reunion yesterday.

286
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:19,700
You should be thinking
about your relationship...

287
00:18:22,533 --> 00:18:23,633
Don't talk nonsense.

288
00:18:23,633 --> 00:18:25,200
There's no problem between them.

289
00:18:28,500 --> 00:18:30,600
I'm not even
the Chairman's biological daughter.

290
00:18:30,800 --> 00:18:33,300
They're not related by blood,
so what's the problem?

291
00:18:35,033 --> 00:18:37,633
Let's eat before we're late.

292
00:18:38,033 --> 00:18:39,233
Please enjoy.

293
00:18:43,700 --> 00:18:46,633
Sorry? You're inviting
Seong Jun and his wife over?

294
00:18:46,833 --> 00:18:48,133
Of course I am.

295
00:18:48,900 --> 00:18:51,300
If she's your mother's daughter,
she's your younger sister.

296
00:18:51,933 --> 00:18:53,633
You should all properly
introduce yourselves again.

297
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:56,000
Yes.

298
00:18:56,800 --> 00:18:58,900
Father, surely you don't intend...

299
00:18:59,200 --> 00:19:01,900
to add Kang Yeon Ja
to the family registry?

300
00:19:02,400 --> 00:19:04,900
Why? Would that be a problem?

301
00:19:06,600 --> 00:19:07,700
Father, I don't think that's...

302
00:19:08,333 --> 00:19:10,233
To be honest, she's not even your blood.

303
00:19:11,500 --> 00:19:13,833
Enough with this outdated obsession
with bloodlines.

304
00:19:14,233 --> 00:19:17,200
Then did your mother raise you
for 50 years because of blood?

305
00:19:17,400 --> 00:19:19,433
That's completely different.

306
00:19:19,600 --> 00:19:20,900
How is it different?

307
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:22,800
It obviously is, Father.

308
00:19:23,300 --> 00:19:27,033
If she's legally registered as family,
it'll complicate all sorts of things.

309
00:19:27,500 --> 00:19:28,633
Inheritance and everything else.

310
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:32,700
There's nothing to worry about.

311
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:36,933
Neither Yeon Sun nor I
have any interest in the family registry.

312
00:19:38,200 --> 00:19:39,433
Do you really mean it, Mother?

313
00:19:40,533 --> 00:19:42,533
That's a very wise decision.

314
00:19:46,733 --> 00:19:47,733
I'm off.

315
00:19:47,733 --> 00:19:50,400
Hey, wait up! I've been waiting for you.

316
00:19:51,300 --> 00:19:54,333
Father, today they're announcing
the second-round winner.

317
00:19:54,600 --> 00:19:56,600
I know. Get to work.

318
00:20:05,533 --> 00:20:08,133
Please, Min Ho. You have to win again.

319
00:20:09,133 --> 00:20:11,800
Why did her name have to be Seo Seung Ri?

320
00:20:11,933 --> 00:20:13,233
I hate even saying it.

321
00:20:14,700 --> 00:20:15,700
Please.

322
00:20:15,700 --> 00:20:18,000
(Kangsu Construction)

323
00:20:18,300 --> 00:20:20,700
Just like the first round,

324
00:20:20,700 --> 00:20:23,600
I have no idea what the results are.

325
00:20:24,333 --> 00:20:26,333
Now then, I'll announce them.

326
00:20:34,200 --> 00:20:35,200
Mr. Cho, you do it.

327
00:20:39,300 --> 00:20:41,300
The second-round results...

328
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:47,133
Team Two wins, 59 to 41.

329
00:20:52,833 --> 00:20:53,933
Congratulations, Team Manager Ko.

330
00:20:54,900 --> 00:20:56,733
You too, Ms. Cho Eun Ae
and Assistant Manager Kim Seong Guk.

331
00:20:56,800 --> 00:20:59,500
Congratulations, Team Manager.
And the rest of the team.

332
00:21:00,200 --> 00:21:01,533
Congratulations, Team Two.

333
00:21:03,633 --> 00:21:05,600
Good work, Team Manager Ko.

334
00:21:06,033 --> 00:21:09,700
The results are so different
from the first round...

335
00:21:09,700 --> 00:21:12,500
that I have to wonder
if they're really fair.

336
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:14,000
No.

337
00:21:14,300 --> 00:21:17,300
We admit our team fell short
in integrating Joy.

338
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:21,033
Well, it's not over yet.

339
00:21:21,200 --> 00:21:24,400
Don't forget, the most crucial third round
is still ahead of us.

340
00:21:25,100 --> 00:21:26,100
Let's go.

341
00:21:30,300 --> 00:21:32,600
By the way,
how many days off did Mr. Han Ji Hun take?

342
00:21:32,933 --> 00:21:35,100
He'll be back at work next week.

343
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:39,100
All right. Team Two, enjoy your victory.

344
00:21:39,500 --> 00:21:42,433
As for us, let's regroup
and prepare for the third round.

345
00:21:46,233 --> 00:21:48,033
Ms. Cho, could I see you for a moment?

346
00:21:48,433 --> 00:21:49,933
Yes, Manager.

347
00:21:54,500 --> 00:21:55,833
What's this?

348
00:21:56,100 --> 00:21:58,833
Actually, I caught Mr. Han Ji Hun...

349
00:21:58,833 --> 00:22:01,400
trying to copy Joy's files
from your computer.

350
00:22:01,800 --> 00:22:02,800
What?

351
00:22:02,900 --> 00:22:05,833
Normally, this would go
to the disciplinary committee,

352
00:22:06,600 --> 00:22:08,800
but there are
some complicated issues involved,

353
00:22:09,033 --> 00:22:11,333
so the Chief and I decided
not to do that for now.

354
00:22:12,100 --> 00:22:15,500
Then, was the security camera footage...

355
00:22:15,733 --> 00:22:17,933
Yes. Mr. Han Ji Hun
was involved in that as well.

356
00:22:18,800 --> 00:22:21,233
I'll leave it up to you
and your team manager.

357
00:22:21,833 --> 00:22:23,800
If you want disciplinary action,
I'll refer it to the committee.

358
00:22:24,233 --> 00:22:26,400
Talk it over with him
and let me know your decision.

359
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:30,733
Personally, I think...

360
00:22:31,233 --> 00:22:34,800
Mr. Han's version of Joy was headed
in a completely different direction,

361
00:22:35,033 --> 00:22:38,500
so even if he saw our files,
it probably wouldn't have hurt us.

362
00:22:39,100 --> 00:22:40,900
As for the security camera footage,

363
00:22:40,900 --> 00:22:43,733
I don't want to make
a bigger issue out of it.

364
00:22:44,533 --> 00:22:46,600
Are you saying
you're willing to let it all go?

365
00:22:46,933 --> 00:22:49,300
Well, I still need to discuss it
with Team Manager,

366
00:22:49,633 --> 00:22:51,900
but I think he'll feel the same way.

367
00:22:53,700 --> 00:22:54,933
Let me know
once you've made your decision.

368
00:22:56,133 --> 00:22:59,200
And I'll apologize for that day,

369
00:22:59,333 --> 00:23:00,500
for what I said on the rooftop.

370
00:23:02,033 --> 00:23:03,133
It's been a while, hasn't it?

371
00:23:04,633 --> 00:23:07,033
When you asked if everything came
that easily to me?

372
00:23:08,333 --> 00:23:10,433
Thank you for apologizing,
even if it's late.

373
00:23:11,533 --> 00:23:14,600
It looks like things are going well
with Team Manager too. Congratulations.

374
00:23:14,933 --> 00:23:15,933
Sorry?

375
00:23:16,133 --> 00:23:18,733
Right. Thank you.

376
00:23:28,100 --> 00:23:31,200
What?
Seung Ri reported a voice phishing scam?

377
00:23:31,600 --> 00:23:34,600
Yes. She suddenly chased after a scammer,

378
00:23:35,200 --> 00:23:36,700
ended up being taken hostage,
and almost got killed.

379
00:23:37,033 --> 00:23:38,700
Fortunately, I followed her,

380
00:23:39,233 --> 00:23:40,633
and the police arrived quickly too,

381
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:42,833
so it ended without anyone
getting seriously hurt.

382
00:23:45,633 --> 00:23:48,633
She begged me not to tell her parents
because they'd worry.

383
00:23:49,300 --> 00:23:50,533
Still, the more I think about it,

384
00:23:50,533 --> 00:23:53,400
the more I feel like
something's bothering her.

385
00:23:57,000 --> 00:23:59,500
Does anything come to mind?

386
00:24:00,433 --> 00:24:03,333
No. I'm just badly shaken.

387
00:24:03,833 --> 00:24:05,300
She's always been too proud...

388
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:08,733
to tell me what's really on her mind.

389
00:24:09,233 --> 00:24:11,500
That's why I had no choice
but to tell you.

390
00:24:12,033 --> 00:24:13,700
Please keep an eye on her.

391
00:24:14,200 --> 00:24:15,200
I will.

392
00:24:15,733 --> 00:24:17,333
- Thanks, Chief Ko.
- Sure.

393
00:24:24,800 --> 00:24:26,733
Seung Ri met Jeong Dong Pal.

394
00:24:27,933 --> 00:24:28,933
That's why...

395
00:24:31,800 --> 00:24:34,200
He wants my wife and me
to come over tonight?

396
00:24:34,900 --> 00:24:36,400
That's right. Your wife.

397
00:24:37,033 --> 00:24:41,100
He's inviting my sister,
Kang Yeon Ja, over.

398
00:24:41,700 --> 00:24:44,600
If you're busy, just let me know.
I'll explain.

399
00:24:45,533 --> 00:24:48,100
I'll talk it over with my wife,
and if we can make it, we'll come.

400
00:24:48,700 --> 00:24:51,000
I should properly introduce myself too.

401
00:24:51,900 --> 00:24:52,900
Properly introduce yourself?

402
00:24:54,100 --> 00:24:57,100
What, now that you're the son-in-law,
you're introducing yourself properly?

403
00:24:57,300 --> 00:24:59,300
Mr. Cho, you haven't forgotten
our agreement, have you?

404
00:25:00,200 --> 00:25:03,800
You said you'd leave the family registry
and Kangsu Group's shares alone?

405
00:25:04,933 --> 00:25:06,733
- I'll get going now.
- Wait.

406
00:25:07,933 --> 00:25:09,300
You know it's been recorded, right?

407
00:25:10,100 --> 00:25:11,300
No changing your story later.

408
00:25:12,233 --> 00:25:13,233
You can go now.

409
00:25:14,600 --> 00:25:15,600
Okay then.

410
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:24,833
Yeah. He's completely out of my hands now.

411
00:25:26,000 --> 00:25:28,400
There's nothing
I can do about him anymore.

412
00:25:30,000 --> 00:25:31,000
It's over.

413
00:25:31,600 --> 00:25:33,800
You've been through so much.

414
00:25:34,533 --> 00:25:35,700
I'm truly sorry.

415
00:25:37,200 --> 00:25:40,033
You lost your mom so suddenly
because of my mistake.

416
00:25:41,300 --> 00:25:43,433
I can't imagine
how hard your life must've been.

417
00:25:45,500 --> 00:25:46,700
No, Chairman.

418
00:25:48,000 --> 00:25:49,400
I'm the one who should be thanking you,

419
00:25:50,033 --> 00:25:52,500
even if it's only now.

420
00:25:53,900 --> 00:25:56,500
I regretted pulling away from you...

421
00:25:57,100 --> 00:25:58,333
that day in the garden.

422
00:25:58,900 --> 00:26:00,300
It was the hand that saved my life.

423
00:26:00,600 --> 00:26:03,133
No. Don't dwell on it.

424
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:07,400
The fact that you're here with us now
is enough.

425
00:26:09,500 --> 00:26:10,800
If I had never found you,

426
00:26:11,900 --> 00:26:14,000
I couldn't have died in peace.

427
00:26:16,400 --> 00:26:19,700
Thank you for being Yeon Sun's family.

428
00:26:20,900 --> 00:26:23,433
I always worried...

429
00:26:24,100 --> 00:26:25,600
that she was all alone somewhere.

430
00:26:26,700 --> 00:26:29,333
Then Eun Ae sent me those family photos,

431
00:26:29,333 --> 00:26:31,033
and I felt such relief.

432
00:26:31,933 --> 00:26:33,300
I realized that,
instead of this inadequate mother,

433
00:26:34,200 --> 00:26:37,300
she'd found a wonderful family
and was living happily.

434
00:26:38,900 --> 00:26:41,000
Thank you for thinking that way.

435
00:26:42,100 --> 00:26:45,600
The more I think about it,
the more amazing this bond feels.

436
00:26:47,400 --> 00:26:48,733
Let's see each other often from now on...

437
00:26:49,500 --> 00:26:52,500
and make up for all the years we lost.

438
00:26:53,200 --> 00:26:54,833
Yes, Chairman. We'd like that.

439
00:26:57,800 --> 00:27:00,333
Now they're having a private meeting
as a couple with Father?

440
00:27:01,100 --> 00:27:03,633
What on earth could they be talking about?

441
00:27:04,000 --> 00:27:06,600
It's been 50 years.
They must have a lot to catch up on.

442
00:27:07,900 --> 00:27:09,800
And technically,
it's not even a private meeting.

443
00:27:09,800 --> 00:27:11,500
A private meeting is one-on-one.

444
00:27:11,500 --> 00:27:14,400
There are four people in there,
so it's a four-way conversation.

445
00:27:15,400 --> 00:27:17,300
Is this really the time for jokes?

446
00:27:17,700 --> 00:27:18,700
Seriously.

447
00:27:19,133 --> 00:27:20,333
- We're home.
- Hey.

448
00:27:22,500 --> 00:27:23,533
Gyeol, did Grandpa invite you too?

449
00:27:23,633 --> 00:27:26,400
Yes. He said
he had something important to discuss.

450
00:27:27,200 --> 00:27:28,233
Where are Grandpa and Grandma?

451
00:27:37,633 --> 00:27:38,733
Looks like everyone's here.

452
00:27:39,500 --> 00:27:40,500
All right. Have a seat.

453
00:27:43,700 --> 00:27:44,700
Now then...

454
00:27:45,300 --> 00:27:48,500
I've finally finished
one of my biggest tasks.

455
00:27:49,633 --> 00:27:52,900
Soon, it'll be time to hold my funeral.

456
00:27:58,700 --> 00:28:01,133
What did you just say, Father?

457
00:28:01,600 --> 00:28:03,600
Your funeral?

458
00:28:04,200 --> 00:28:06,300
Yes. My funeral.

459
00:28:07,033 --> 00:28:08,033
Grandpa...

460
00:28:27,700 --> 00:28:29,400
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
